Great question! Decorators in Python can be implemented in a class method by using the `@` symbol to define a decorator function that takes a single argument, which is the function to be decorated. Here's an example:
```
class MyClass:
    def my_method(self):
        # This is the method that will be decorated
        return "This is the original method"

    @my_decorator
    def my_method(self):
        # This is the decor
